cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.SY 

This paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper specifically focuses on relay scheduling policies, which are related to network protocols and optimization, and hence could also fall under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). The paper also involves mathematical optimization techniques, which could be categorized under cs.SI (systems and control) or cs.MM (mathematical optimization). Finally, the paper deals with the design and analysis of communication systems, which could be categorized under cs.SY (systems and control).
